WEBVTT

00:00.367 --> 00:04.715
ï»¿In 1999, he was dispatched from Renault to the near bankrupt Nissan.

00:05.389 --> 00:09.749
Nissan is one of Japan's top 3 automakers alongside Toyota and Honda...

00:10.017 --> 00:13.735
...and Ghosn restored it to profitability in a year by closing factories...

00:13.815 --> 00:17.029
...and breaking up close-knit supplier networks to save costs.

00:17.412 --> 00:20.773
Under Ghosn, Nissan introduced the all-electric Leaf.

00:20.987 --> 00:23.841
It says the Leaf is the world's best-selling electric vehicle...

00:24.437 --> 00:26.636
...but sales have fallen well below initial goal.

00:26.913 --> 00:29.072
More recently, Nissan's Note model,...

00:29.424 --> 00:31.699
...which includes a hybrid version with an electric motor,...

00:31.919 --> 00:35.079
...has supplanted Toyota's Prius as Japan's best-selling model.

00:35.482 --> 00:38.441
The Renault-Nissan Alliance plans to sell 10 models...

00:38.538 --> 00:40.948
...with autonomous driving technology by 2020.

00:41.273 --> 00:44.379
And Ghosn is expected to stay active in charting the company's path.

